The stock of Philip Morris Cos rosetoday following recommendations by First Boston Corp and MorganStanley and Co, traders said.    Philip Morris gained 1-3/4 to 88-1/4.    First Boston's analyst was unavailable for comment.    Morgan Stanley's David Hill said he just assumed coverageof Philip Morris and placed it on his recommended list becasueof its attractive earnings growth and because the stock isselling at a discount to the market based on Morgan's figures.Hill expects Morris to earn 7.75 dlrs a share this year and9.50 dlrs in 1988. In 1986, Morris earned 6.20 dlrs a share. Reuter&#3;